How we help

Patient solutions

Scriptagram was founded by Chris Cosse, an orthodontist who recognized the need to educate patients. He started making videos to explain complex concepts and procedures in simple, easy-to-understand terms. After those videos were successful, his clients demanded more, and braces academy was born. Today, Scriptagram continues to develop innovative products to support orthodontists, dentists, and other medical professionals. Braces Academy and OrthoScreening have evolved to boost patient engagement through personalized text messages, social media, and integration, all while continuing to expand the needs of patient education and remote monitoring.

Braces Academy

With Braces Academy, you can educate your patients in a digitally HIPAA compliant manner, directly to their smartphones and their parents phones. Gone are the days of relying solely on in-person consultations or sending home printed materials. Braces Academy provides a convenient and accessible platform to deliver educational content. By utilizing this system, you can ensure that your patients and their parents have all the information they need to make informed decisions about their orthodontic treatment. From treatment options and procedures to oral hygiene instructions and care tips, Braces Academy covers a wide range of topics, all in a user-friendly and engaging format.

Ortho Screening

Develop your patient pipeline with virtual screenings.

OrthoScreening offers you the freedom to treat patients outside of the traditional office setting, breaking the barriers of time and location. This innovative system allows you to conduct screenings and remotely monitor both new and current patients. With OrthoScreening, you can evaluate patients orthodontic needs, assess treatment progress, and make necessary adjustments, all without them having to visit your practice. This flexibility is especially beneficial for patients who may have difficulty accessing your office due to distance, transportation, or other constraints. By embracing remote monitoring, you can provide convenient care that accommodates your patients busy lives. With OrthoScreening, you are also given a library of Braces Academy videos to help explain reporting.
